# When `.npmignore` is present, npm stops consulting `.gitignore`
# for pack exclusions. The `files` array in package.json is the
# primary allowlist; this file just keeps npm from re-vetoing what
# `files` already permits.
#
# Specifically: without this empty `.npmignore`, the root `.gitignore`'s
# `vendor/` line drops the entire vendor tree from the tarball, even
# though `vendor/excalidraw-mcp/dist/**` is in `files`. We ship the
# pre-built MCP because consumer-side postinstall is fragile under
# `--ignore-scripts`, offline mirrors, and corporate CI sandboxes.
